Q: 2) Write a PHP script for the following: Design a form to accept two strings from
the user. Find the first occurrence and the last occurrence of the small string in the
large string. Also count the total number of occurrences of small string in the large
string. Provide a text box to accept a string, which will replace the small string in the
large string. (Use built-in functions)

-:--
<html>
	<body>
		<form action="prg2.php" method="post">
		Enter the string
		<input type="text" name="str">
		<br>
		<br>
		Enter substring
		<input type="text" name="s">
		<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		Enter string Replace
		<input type="text" name="r">
		<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		First Occurrence
		<input type="radio" name="op" value="F">
		<br>
		<br>
		
		Last Occurrence
		<input type="radio" name="op" value="L">
		<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		Replace
		<input type="radio" name="op" value="R">
		<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		<input type="submit" value="SEND">
		<br>
		<br>
		<br>
			<?php
if(isset($_POST['str']) || isset($_POST['s']) || isset($_POST['r']))
				{
					 $str=$_POST['str'];
					 $s=$_POST['s'];
					$r=$_POST['r'];
					$op=$_POST['op'];

				if($op=="F")
				{
			echo $c = strpos($str,$s);
				}
				if($op=="L")
				{
				echo $l = strrpos($str,$s);
				}
			if($op=="R")
				{
						
				echo str_replace($s,$r,$str);
						
						
				}
				}
			?>
				</form>
			</body>
	</html>
					

 
